    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200 text-justify space-y-6">
      <p>
        I am a <strong>Research Scientist</strong> at <a href="https://www.unimore.it">UniMORE</a> (University of Modena and Reggio Emilia),
        Department of Engineering "Enzo Ferrari", focusing on the application of <strong>Artificial Intelligence</strong>
        and <strong>Machine Learning</strong> to challenging problems in process and supply chain optimization.
      </p>

      <p>
        In December 2023, I obtained the <strong>ASN</strong> (Abilitazione Scientifica Nazionale),
        qualifying me for the position of Associate Professor in Industrial Mechanical Systems.
      </p>

      <p>
        My research is currently funded through the <strong>ECOSISTER</strong> project (PNRR - National Recovery and Resilience Plan),
        Spoke 3 "Green manufacturing for a sustainable economy", developing innovative data-driven and lean-based solutions
        for sustainable production planning and control systems.
      </p>

      <p>
        I am also Co-Founder of <a href="https://kheperer.it" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Kheperer</a>,
        a startup revolutionizing how AI and ML are applied to achieve tangible goals in Industry 4.0.
      </p>

      <p>
        Beyond research, I am a proficient <strong>Full-stack Developer</strong>, leveraging Python, JavaScript, and SQL
        to build state-of-the-art business web applications and deliver value through pragmatic application of
        cutting-edge machine learning techniques.
      </p>
    </div>
